value.title: Biden administration unable to continue $300 weekly pandemic unemployment benefits that GOP governors are slashing
value.excerpt: The Labor Department has exhausted its options for continuing to pay an extra $300 a week in federal unemployment benefits to jobless people in the 22 GOP-led states that are ending them early, an administration official told CNN Thursday.

value.title: Trump administration secretly obtained CNN reporter's phone and email records

value.title: U.S. waives sanctions on Nord Stream 2 as Biden seeks to mend Europe ties
